Scheduled bus transport is a vital segment of the transportation industry that plays a crucial role in providing convenient and affordable commuting options for millions of people worldwide. The market can be segmented based on service type, bus type, distance, and booking type. In terms of service type, scheduled bus transport services can be categorized into private and public sectors, each catering to distinct market segments. Private bus services are more customized and often focus on specific routes, while public bus services offer more general routes to serve the broader population. Bus types also vary, ranging from single-decker to double-decker and articulated buses, each offering different passenger capacities and amenities. Segmentation by distance includes short-distance and long-distance bus services, with each targeting commuters with specific travel needs. Moreover, booking types such as online and offline options further differentiate the market's offerings, catering to diverse consumer preferences.

